\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7754408 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12789151\charrsid8990217 
What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be? Did they bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7612654 TW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12789151\charrsid8990217 Y
es, they were religious, my parents were. We always went to Church. As a family we went to Church together. And I and my brother went to Sunday School. Sunday, I suppose from the age of 7 to 14 or 15 was largely Sunday School, and then Church. Sunday Scho
ol in the afternoon and then often Church in the evening. In the winter we didn't go to Church in the evenings quite so frequently.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid7754408 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12789151\charrsid8990217 
Your parents would consider some things definitely wrong, and some things right to do, and want you to do?
